# Repo-root build context excludes. Applies to the two builds whose compose
# context is the repo root: frontend (frontend/Dockerfile) and docs
# (docs-site/Dockerfile). It SUPERSEDES frontend/.dockerignore and
# docs-site/.dockerignore for those builds, so it must reproduce their excludes.
# The backend/mcp images keep their own package-scoped contexts and .dockerignore.
#
# Keep only what the two image builds COPY: frontend/, docs-site/, shared/
# (each package's package-lock.json + nginx.conf included). Everything below is
# rebuilt inside the image, is another package, or is tooling/secrets that must
# never enter the context.

# Rebuilt inside the image
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.vitepress/cache
**/coverage
**/*.tsbuildinfo
.turbo

# VCS, CI, and secrets (.env* keeps the committed .env.prod out of the context)
.git
.gitignore
.github
.env*

# Other packages / not needed by the frontend or docs builds
backend
mcp
e2e
contract
skill
deployments
scripts
docs
.ruff_cache

# Root tooling and scratch
docker-compose*.yml
justfile
ruff.toml
.DS_Store
